<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362420>
    dc:description "FIGURE 37. Pholcus phoenixus sp. nov. A. epigynum, ventral view. B. same, dorsal view. C. male body, dorsal view. D. trochanter of male left palp, dorsal view. E. male left chelicera, frontal view. F. male sternum, ventral view. G. left procursus, dorsal view. H. left palp, prolateral view. I. same, retrolateral view. Scale lines: 1.0mm (C), 0.5mm (A, B, E–I), 0.2mm (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5362420/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362422>
    dc:description "FIGURE 38. Pholcus phoenixus sp. nov. A. tip of female palp, showing tarsal organ. B. epigynum, ventral view. C. embolus and uncus of male left bulb, retrolateral view. D. trochanter of male left palp, with modified hair on the tip of ventral apophysis. E. tip of male distal cheliceral apophysis. F. male cheliceral apophyses proximolaterally and proximocentrally, front view. G. tarsal organ on male tarsus 1. H. male palpal tarsal organ, prolateral view. I. pseudosegmentation on male tarsus 1." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5362422/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

